Sentencas: Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 (SDC) dense electrolyte thin film, La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF) porous cathode layer and Ni-SDC anode functional layer for anode-supported SOFCs are fabricated by a slurry spin coating technique.
Titulo: Fabrication and performance of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells via slurry spin coating

Sentencas: The optimum conditions for preparing the single cell with a uniform microstructure as well as excellent performance have been investigated.
Titulo: Fabrication and performance of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells via slurry spin coating

Sentencas: A dense electrolyte thin film with a crack-free microstructure can be obtained by using the SDC powders pre-calcined at 900 degrees C.
Titulo: Fabrication and performance of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells via slurry spin coating

Sentencas: The power density of the cells increases with the increasing weight content of corn starch (corn starch wt.%), which is mainly ascribed to the decrease of the concentration loss in the anode.
Titulo: Fabrication and performance of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells via slurry spin coating

Sentencas: However, the trade-off between the single cell performance and mechanical strength results in the optimum composition being obtained for the Ni-SDC anode containing 15 wt.% corn starch (15-Ni-SDC).
Titulo: Fabrication and performance of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells via slurry spin coating

Sentencas: In contrast to the data in the literatures, the relatively large ohmic resistance (R-ohm) values in the present study are obtained for the 15-Ni-SDC cell.
Titulo: Fabrication and performance of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells via slurry spin coating

Sentencas: In order to further improve the cell performance, an anode functional layer is introduced.
Titulo: Fabrication and performance of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells via slurry spin coating

Sentencas: The power density of the resulting single cell is evidently increased, exhibiting the excellent maximum power densities of 685, 472 and 275 mW cm(-2) at 600, 550 and 500 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Fabrication and performance of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells via slurry spin coating
